    <P paraDef="topic_title"><MkDest id="#unique_1"/>Customization</P>
    <!--STARTSECTION $outputclass=[]-->
    <!--topic/title parent concept count=1 outputclass=-->
    <!--STARTSECTION $outputclass=[]-->
    <P paraDef="topic_title1"><MkDest id="#unique_2"/>Customizing the com.miramo.mmpdf plugin</P>
    <P paraDef="body">The <!--topic/ph hi-d found: [b] id=--><Font fontDef="b"
            >com.miramo.mmpdf</Font> plugin is intended to cover most formatting requirements, but
        in some cases it may be necessary to create a custom plugin which overrides or adds to some
        of the features supported by the standard plugin. If so,
            <!--topic/ph hi-d found: [b] id=--><Font fontDef="b">do not</Font> modify the files in
        the default <Font fontDef="glossterm">MiramoPDF DITA-OT plugin</Font> installation folder
            (<!--SW-D FOUND--><Font fontDef="filepath">DITA-OT3.x\plugins\com.miramo.mmpdf</Font>),
        because these files will be overwritten when you install a new version of the MiramoPDF
        DITA-OT plugin. Create a custom MiramoPDF DITA-OT plugin instead.</P>
    <Tbl tblDef="fig">
        <TblColumn width="1*">
            <TblColumnFormat align="start"/>
        </TblColumn>
        <Row keepTogether="N">
            <Cell>
                <AFrame wrap="Y" position="inline" crop="N" startIndent="inherit" align="start">
                    <!--makeImage 0-->
                    <Image file="graphics/default_miramo_dita-ot_plugin.png" keepAspectRatio="Y"
                        dpi="240"/>
                </AFrame>
                <AFrame wrap="Y" position="inline" crop="N" startIndent="inherit" align="start">
                    <!--makeImage 0-->
                    <Image file="graphics/custom_miramo_dita-ot_plugin.png" keepAspectRatio="Y"
                        dpi="240"/>
                </AFrame>


                <P paraDef="dt">A</P>
                <P paraDef="dd"><!--topic/ph hi-d found: [b] id=--><Font fontDef="b">Default</Font>
                    MiramoPDF DITA-OT plugin folder</P>


                <P paraDef="dt">B</P>
                <P paraDef="dd"><!--topic/ph hi-d found: [b] id=--><Font fontDef="b">Custom</Font>
                    MiramoPDF DITA-OT plugin folder</P>


            </Cell>
        </Row>
    </Tbl>
    <P paraDef="body">If you have access to oXygenXML Author/Editor see <XRef id="#unique_3"
            xRefDef="xref"/>, otherwise follow the instructions in <XRef id="#unique_4"
            xRefDef="xref"/> or <XRef id="#unique_5" xRefDef="xref"/></P>
    <P paraDef="body">It also includes a simple example of working with a new plugin
        (com.example.my-mmpdf) to create a new transformation type my-mmpdf which includes changes
        to localization text, default parameter values and to the DITA to MiramoXML
        transformation.</P>
    <!--STARTSECTION $outputclass=[]-->
    <!--topic/title parent concept count=2 outputclass=-->
    <!--STARTSECTION $outputclass=[]-->
    <P paraDef="topic_title2"><MkDest id="#unique_3"/>Creating a custom MiramoPDF DITA-OT plugin
        using oXygenXML Author/Editor</P>
    <!--TOPIC METADATA (- topic/prolog ) START-->
    <VarDef varDef="author">Yves</VarDef>
    <MetaData name="creator">Yves</MetaData>
    <!--TOPIC METADATA END-->
    <!--PASS-THRU: section @class=- topic/section -->
    <P paraDef="body"><MkDest id="#unique_3_Connect_42_context_tr1_rml_k3b"/>This topic describes
        how to use the <!--topic/ph hi-d found: [b] id=--><Font fontDef="b">MiramoPDF - generate new
            plugin</Font> transformation scenario in oXygenXML Author/Editor to create a new custom
        plugin.</P>

    <!--PASS-THRU: section @class=- topic/section -->
    <ParaGroup paraGroupDef="ol">
        <!--topic/li-->
        <!--p element nested in list at nest level 6-->
        <!--makeListPara p-->
        <P paraDef="orderedlistitem1" numberValue="1" withPrevious="Y">In oXygenXML Author/Editor,
            choose <Font fontDef="menucascade"><Font fontDef="uicontrol">Options</Font><Var
                    varDef="menucascadeseparator"/><Font fontDef="uicontrol">Import Transformation
                    Scenarios</Font></Font>.</P>

        <!--topic/li-->
        <!--p element nested in list at nest level 6-->
        <!--makeListPara p-->
        <P paraDef="orderedlistitem1">Navigate to your MiramoPDF DITA-OT plugin installation folder,
            for example <!--SW-D FOUND--><Font fontDef="filepath">C:\Program Files\Oxygen XML Editor
                21\frameworks\dita\DITA-OT3.x\plugins\com.miramo.mmpdf\integration\oxygen</Font>
            .</P>

        <!--topic/li-->
        <!--p element nested in list at nest level 6-->
        <!--makeListPara p-->
        <P paraDef="orderedlistitem1">Select <!--SW-D FOUND--><Font fontDef="filepath"
                >MiramoPDF-generate-plugin.scenarios</Font> and click <Font fontDef="uicontrol"
                >Open</Font>.</P>

        <!--topic/li-->
        <!--p element nested in list at nest level 6-->
        <!--makeListPara p-->
        <P paraDef="orderedlistitem1">In the <Font fontDef="wintitle">Import scenarios</Font>
            dialog, select <Font fontDef="uicontrol">Project Options</Font> and click <Font
                fontDef="uicontrol">Import</Font>.</P>
        <!--PASS-THRU: itemgroup @class=- topic/itemgroup -->
        <Tbl tblDef="fig">
            <TblColumn width="1*">
                <TblColumnFormat align="start"/>
            </TblColumn>
            <Row keepTogether="N">
                <Cell>
                    <AFrame wrap="Y" position="inline" crop="N" startIndent="inherit" align="start">
                        <!--makeImage 0-->
                        <Image file="graphics/import_scenarios.png" keepAspectRatio="Y" dpi="144"/>
                    </AFrame>
                </Cell>
            </Row>
        </Tbl>


        <!--topic/li-->
        <!--p element nested in list at nest level 6-->
        <!--makeListPara p-->
        <P paraDef="orderedlistitem1">Create or open any DITA file.</P>
        <!--PASS-THRU: itemgroup @class=- topic/itemgroup -->
        <!--p element nested in list at nest level 6-->
        <!--makeListPara p-->
        <P paraDef="orderedlistitem1" listLabel="N"><MkDest id="#unique_3_Connect_42_p_ctd_wgz_fjb"
            />You can open a DITA file in the following <!--SW-D FOUND--><Font fontDef="filepath"
                >Samples</Font> folder: </P>
        <!--p element nested in list at nest level 6-->
        <!--makeListPara p-->
        <P paraDef="orderedlistitem1" listLabel="N">
            <!--SW-D FOUND-->
            <Font fontDef="filepath">C:\Program Files\Oxygen XML Editor
                21\frameworks\dita\DITA-OT3.x\plugins\com.miramo.mmpdf\samples\flowers</Font>
        </P>


        <!--topic/li-->
        <!--p element nested in list at nest level 6-->
        <!--makeListPara p-->
        <P paraDef="orderedlistitem1">Click the <Font fontDef="uicontrol">Configure Transformation
                Scenario</Font>
            <AFrame wrap="Y" position="inline" crop="N" startIndent="inherit" align="start"
                    ><!--makeImage 0--><Image
                    file="graphics/configure_transformation_scenario_button.png" keepAspectRatio="Y"
                /></AFrame> button.</P>

        <!--topic/li-->
        <!--p element nested in list at nest level 6-->
        <!--makeListPara p-->
        <P paraDef="orderedlistitem1">In the <Font fontDef="wintitle">Configure Transformation
                Scenarios</Font> dialog, select the <Font fontDef="uicontrol">MiramoPDF - generate
                new plugin</Font> transformation scenario and click <Font fontDef="uicontrol"
                >Edit</Font>.</P>

        <!--topic/li-->
        <!--p element nested in list at nest level 6-->
        <!--makeListPara p-->
        <P paraDef="orderedlistitem1">Click the <Font fontDef="uicontrol">Parameters</Font> tab and
            change the <Font fontDef="uicontrol">plugin-name</Font> and <Font fontDef="uicontrol"
                >transtype</Font> parameters, as shown in the example below.</P>
        <!--PASS-THRU: itemgroup @class=- topic/itemgroup -->
        <!--p element nested in list at nest level 6-->
        <!--makeListPara p-->
        <P paraDef="orderedlistitem1" listLabel="N">A <Font fontDef="uicontrol">transtype</Font> is
            a new transformation type with any new custom parameters that are supported. In this
            case, the <Font fontDef="uicontrol">transtype</Font> is the MiramoPDF transformation
            with customizations done in a <!--SW-D FOUND--><Font fontDef="filepath"
                >custom.xsl</Font> file.</P>
        <Tbl tblDef="fig">
            <TblColumn width="1*">
                <TblColumnFormat align="start"/>
            </TblColumn>
            <Row keepTogether="N">
                <Cell>
                    <AFrame wrap="Y" position="inline" crop="N" startIndent="inherit" align="start">
                        <!--makeImage 0-->
                        <Image file="graphics/edit_ant_scenario.png" keepAspectRatio="Y" dpi="144"/>
                    </AFrame>
                </Cell>
            </Row>
        </Tbl>


        <!--topic/li-->
        <!--p element nested in list at nest level 6-->
        <!--makeListPara p-->
        <P paraDef="orderedlistitem1">Click <Font fontDef="uicontrol">OK</Font> and then <Font
                fontDef="uicontrol">Apply associated</Font> to run the transformation scenario.</P>
        <!--Using default mapping of class - topic/itemgroup  on element itemgroup to body paragraph -->
        <P paraDef="body">In your DITA-OT installation folder, you will now find your custom Miramo
            plugin folder where you can make the necessary customizations in the
                <!--SW-D FOUND--><Font fontDef="filepath">cfg\xsl\custom.xsl</Font> file.<Tbl
                tblDef="fig"><TblColumn width="1*"><TblColumnFormat align="start"/></TblColumn><Row
                    keepTogether="N"><Cell>
                        <AFrame wrap="Y" position="inline" crop="N" startIndent="inherit"
                            align="start"><!--makeImage 0--><Image file="graphics/custom_xsl.png"
                                keepAspectRatio="Y" dpi="144"/></AFrame>
                    </Cell></Row></Tbl></P>

        <!--topic/li-->
        <!--p element nested in list at nest level 6-->
        <!--makeListPara p-->
        <P paraDef="orderedlistitem1">Choose <Font fontDef="menucascade"><Font fontDef="uicontrol"
                    >Options</Font><Var varDef="menucascadeseparator"/><Font fontDef="uicontrol"
                    >Import Transformation Scenarios</Font></Font>.</P>

        <!--topic/li-->
        <!--p element nested in list at nest level 6-->
        <!--makeListPara p-->
        <P paraDef="orderedlistitem1">Navigate to your newly created, custom MiramoPDF DITA-OT
            plugin folder.</P>
        <!--Using default mapping of class - topic/itemgroup  on element itemgroup to body paragraph -->
        <P paraDef="body">For example: <HyperCmd fontDef="ulink"
                openURL="file:///C:/Program%20Files/Oxygen%20XML%20Editor%2021/frameworks/dita/DITA-OT3.x/plugins/com.example.my-mmpdf"
                    ><!--SW-D FOUND--><Font fontDef="filepath">C:\Program Files\Oxygen XML Editor
                    21\frameworks\dita\DITA-OT3.x\plugins\com.miramo.flow-mmpdf</Font></HyperCmd>
            .</P>

        <!--topic/li-->
        <!--p element nested in list at nest level 6-->
        <!--makeListPara p-->
        <P paraDef="orderedlistitem1">Select the .scenarios file, for example <!--SW-D FOUND--><Font
                fontDef="filepath">com.miramo.flow-mmpdf.scenarios</Font>, and click <Font
                fontDef="uicontrol">Open</Font>.</P>

        <!--topic/li-->
        <!--p element nested in list at nest level 6-->
        <!--makeListPara p-->
        <P paraDef="orderedlistitem1">In the <Font fontDef="wintitle">Import scenarios</Font>
            dialog, select <Font fontDef="uicontrol">Project Options</Font> and click <Font
                fontDef="uicontrol">Import</Font>.</P>
        <!--PASS-THRU: itemgroup @class=- topic/itemgroup -->
        <Tbl tblDef="fig">
            <TblColumn width="1*">
                <TblColumnFormat align="start"/>
            </TblColumn>
            <Row keepTogether="N">
                <Cell>
                    <AFrame wrap="Y" position="inline" crop="N" startIndent="inherit" align="start">
                        <!--makeImage 0-->
                        <Image file="graphics/import_custom_plugin.png" keepAspectRatio="Y"
                            dpi="144"/>
                    </AFrame>
                </Cell>
            </Row>
        </Tbl>


        <!--topic/li-->
        <!--p element nested in list at nest level 6-->
        <!--makeListPara p-->
        <P paraDef="orderedlistitem1">Click the <Font fontDef="uicontrol">Configure Transformation
                Scenario</Font>
            <AFrame wrap="Y" position="inline" crop="N" startIndent="inherit" align="start"
                    ><!--makeImage 0--><Image
                    file="graphics/configure_transformation_scenario_button.png" keepAspectRatio="Y"
                /></AFrame> button again.</P>
        <!--Using default mapping of class - topic/itemgroup  on element itemgroup to body paragraph -->
        <P paraDef="body">Your new custom <Font fontDef="glossterm">Miramo</Font> transformation
            scenario is now ready for use.<Tbl tblDef="fig"><TblColumn width="1*"><TblColumnFormat
                        align="start"/></TblColumn><Row keepTogether="N"><Cell>
                        <AFrame wrap="Y" position="inline" crop="N" startIndent="inherit"
                            align="start"><!--makeImage 0--><Image
                                file="graphics/example_custom_scenario.png" keepAspectRatio="Y"
                                dpi="144"/></AFrame>
                    </Cell></Row></Tbl></P>

        <!--topic/li-->
        <!--p element nested in list at nest level 6-->
        <!--makeListPara p-->
        <P paraDef="orderedlistitem1">You can click <Font fontDef="uicontrol">Apply
                associated</Font> to test your custom transformation scenario.</P>

    </ParaGroup>
    <!--STARTSECTION $outputclass=[]-->
    <!--topic/title parent concept count=2 outputclass=-->
    <!--STARTSECTION $outputclass=[]-->
    <P paraDef="topic_title2"><MkDest id="#unique_6"/>Manually creating a custom MiramoPDF DITA-OT
        plugin</P>
    <!--STARTSECTION $outputclass=[]-->
    <!--topic/title parent concept count=3 outputclass=-->
    <!--STARTSECTION $outputclass=[]-->
    <P paraDef="topic_title3"><MkDest id="#unique_4"/>Manually creating a new custom plugin</P>
    <P paraDef="body">The com.miramo.mmpdf folder includes a sub-folder called com.example.my-mmpdf,
        and creates a transformation type 'my-mmpdf'. See <XRef id="#unique_5" xRefDef="xref"/> for
        information on creating a company specific plugin with a differently named plugin and
        transformation type.</P>
    <P paraDef="body">To create a new custom plugin 'com.example.my-mmpdf', start by copying this
        folder to the DITA-OT plugins folder so it is at the same level as the original
        com.miramo.mmpdf folder.</P>
    <!--STARTSECTION $outputclass=[]-->
    <!--topic/title parent concept count=3 outputclass=-->
    <!--STARTSECTION $outputclass=[]-->
    <P paraDef="topic_title3"><MkDest id="#unique_5"/>Manually creating a company specific
        plugin</P>
    <P paraDef="body">In some cases it may be necessary to create one or more new plugins with a
        different names, targets, and transformation types.</P>
    <P paraDef="body">For example, company ABC Corp might need to create two specializations,
        com.abc.mmpdfl and com.abc.mmpdf2, which create transformation types mmpdfl and mmpdf2
        respectively.</P>
    <P paraDef="body">To do this, copy the <!--SW-D FOUND--><Font fontDef="filepath"
            >plugins/com.miramo.mmpdf/com.example.my-mmpdf</Font> folder to <!--SW-D FOUND--><Font
            fontDef="filepath">plugins/com.abc.mmpdf1</Font> and <!--SW-D FOUND--><Font
            fontDef="filepath">plugins/com.abc.mmpdf2</Font>.</P>
    <P paraDef="body">Then edit the following files in each of the two new folders com.abc.mmpdf1,
        com.abc.mmpdf2:</P>
    <ParaGroup paraGroupDef="ul">
        <!--topic/li-->
        <!--makeListPara li-->
        <P paraDef="unorderedlistitem1" numberValue="1" withPrevious="Y"><MkDest
                id="#unique_5_Connect_42_ul_ypv_h53_ghb"/>plugin.xml</P>
        <!--topic/li-->
        <!--makeListPara li-->
        <P paraDef="unorderedlistitem1"><MkDest id="#unique_5_Connect_42_ul_ypv_h53_ghb"
            />conductor.xml</P>
        <!--topic/li-->
        <!--makeListPara li-->
        <P paraDef="unorderedlistitem1"><MkDest id="#unique_5_Connect_42_ul_ypv_h53_ghb"
            />build.xml</P>
    </ParaGroup>
    <P paraDef="body">Replace all occurrences of 'com.example.my-mmpdf' with com.abc.mmpdf1 or
        com.abc.mmpdf2</P>
    <P paraDef="body">Replace all occurrences of 'my-mmpdf' with 'mmpdf1' or 'mmpdf2'</P>
    <P paraDef="body">Modify xsl/dita2miramo.xsl, cfg/xsl/custom.xsl, cfg/strings/langlist.xml,
        cfg/strings/*.xml as required</P>
    <P paraDef="body">Run the DITA-OT integration process</P>
    <P paraDef="body">The ant targets 'dita2mmpdf1' and 'dita2mmpdf2' will now be available, along
        with the transformation types 'mmpdf1' and 'mmpdf2'.</P>
    <!--STARTSECTION $outputclass=[]-->
    <!--topic/title parent concept count=3 outputclass=-->
    <!--STARTSECTION $outputclass=[]-->
    <P paraDef="topic_title3"><MkDest id="#unique_7"/>Running the DITA-OT integration tool</P>
    <P paraDef="body">Next, install the new com.example.my-mmpdf plugin by running the DITA-OT ant
        integration tool as enabled by your CMS or authoring tool, or using one of the commands
        below.</P>
    <P paraDef="body">For oXygen, see <XRef id="#unique_8" xRefDef="xref"/>.</P>
    <P paraDef="body">For standalone DITA-OT installations, use:</P>
    <P paraDef="lines" whiteSpaceCollapse="N">ant -f integrator.xml</P>
    <P paraDef="body">or use the dita command:</P>
    <P paraDef="lines" whiteSpaceCollapse="N">dita-ot-dir/bin/dita --install</P>
    <P paraDef="body">This will create a new transformation type 'my-mmpdf' which you can use in
        place of the 'mmpdf' transfomation type. It will also add a new ant target
        'dita2my-mmpdf'.</P>
    <P paraDef="body">The next stage is to modify the files in the <!--SW-D FOUND--><Font
            fontDef="filepath">plugins/com.example.my-mmpdf</Font> folder.</P>
    <!--STARTSECTION $outputclass=[]-->
    <!--topic/title parent concept count=2 outputclass=-->
    <!--STARTSECTION $outputclass=[]-->
    <P paraDef="topic_title2"><MkDest id="#unique_9"/>com.example.my-mmpdf files and folders</P>
    <P paraDef="body">The com.example.my-mmpdf plugin includes the following files and folders:</P>


    <P paraDef="dt">&lt;dita-ot-installdir&gt;/plugins/com.example.my-mmpdf</P>

    <P paraDef="dd">Source for my-mmpdf plugin:</P>



    <P paraDef="dt">plugin.xml</P>

    <P paraDef="dd">Configuration file for the com.example.my-mmpdf plugin which creates a new
        transformation type 'my-mmpdf'.</P>



    <P paraDef="dt">conductor.xml</P>

    <P paraDef="dd">Imports local build.xml</P>



    <P paraDef="dt">build.xml</P>

    <P paraDef="dd">Contains the dita2my-mmpdf target, applied by the 'my-mmpdf' transformation
        type.</P>



    <P paraDef="dt">xsl/dita2miramo.xsl</P>

    <P paraDef="dd">Top level stylesheet - modify this file to set default values for xslt
        parameters</P>



    <P paraDef="dt">cfg/strings/langlist.xml</P>

    <P paraDef="dd">Language configuration file including a list of files containing localization
        strings</P>



    <P paraDef="dt">cfg/strings/*.xml</P>

    <P paraDef="dd">Miramo specific localization strings, supplied in addition to the standard
        DITA-OT localization strings (including those in pdf2)</P>



    <P paraDef="dt">cfg/xsl/custom.xsl</P>

    <P paraDef="dd">Modify this file to add xsl stylesheet template match modifications; included by
        xsl/dita2miramo.xsl</P>



    <P paraDef="dt">cfg/xsl/functionstubs.xsl</P>

    <P paraDef="dd">Modify this file to add to or override templates and functions with extension
        points defined in the com.miramo.mmpdf/xsl/utilities.xsl. Included by cfg/xsl/custom.xsl</P>



    <!--STARTSECTION $outputclass=[]-->
    <!--topic/title parent concept count=2 outputclass=-->
    <!--STARTSECTION $outputclass=[]-->
    <P paraDef="topic_title2"><MkDest id="#unique_10"/>Setting default parameter values</P>
    <P paraDef="body">Modify the &lt;xsl:param&gt; and &lt;xsl:variable&gt; definitions in
            <!--SW-D FOUND--><Font fontDef="filepath">custom/xsl/dita2miramo.xsl</Font> as required.
        For example, to set all non-inline graphics to be centered rather than start-aligned by
        default, include this:</P>
    <P paraDef="lines" whiteSpaceCollapse="N">&lt;!-- Default left/right alignment of images within
        text column or text frame.<br/>Allowed values: start center end --&gt;<br/>&lt;xsl:variable
        name="defaultImageAlignment"&gt;center&lt;/xsl:variable&gt;</P>
    <!--STARTSECTION $outputclass=[]-->
    <!--topic/title parent concept count=2 outputclass=-->
    <!--STARTSECTION $outputclass=[]-->
    <P paraDef="topic_title2"><MkDest id="#unique_11"/>Modifying the dita2mmpdf default
        transformation</P>
    <P paraDef="body">Edit the 'cfg/xsl/custom.xsl' stylesheet to add &lt;xsl:template&gt;s to
        achieve the required mapping from DITA elements and attributes to MiramoXML elements and
        attributes. (See the mmComposer reference guide for a detailed description of the MiramoXML
        file format).</P>
    <P paraDef="body">&lt;xsl:template&gt;s added here may either override or add to the
